\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. davidii} Franchet,{\i  Nouv. Arch. Mus. Hist. Nat. Paris} ser. 2, {\b 10}: 65 (1887). Deciduous shrub 1-5 m. Twigs bluntly angled or almost terete, tomentose. Leaves 10-25 cm, ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate, acuminate, serrate, thinly pubescent to almost glabrous above, tomentose beneath, shortly petiolate. Flowers in dense many-flowered cymes, forming a terminal panicle. Young twigs, peduncles, pedicels and calyx tomentose. Corolla pale lilac to deep violet with an orange ring at the mouth, stellate-pubescent and glandular outside; tube 4-5 times as long as calyx, straight; stamens inserted about the middle of the tube.{\i  Cultivated for ornament and commonly naturalized in parts of W. & C. Europe.} [Au Be Br Ga Ge Hb He Ho Hs It.] ({\i China}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. B. albiflora} Hemsley, {\i Jour. Linn. Soc. London} ({\i Bot.}) {\b 26}: 118 (1889). Like {\b 1} but up to 10 m; twigs glabrescent; corolla pale lilac, the tube 2-3 times as long as calyx; stamens inserted near the top of the tube.{\i  Sometimes cultivated for ornament and occasionally naturalized in France.}[ Ga.] ({\i W. China}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. B. japonica} Hemsley,{\i  op. cit.} 119 (1889). Deciduous shrub up to 1·5 m. Twigs sharply 4-angled, with winged angles, stellate-pubescent. Leaves 8-20 cm, ovate-lanceolate, acuminate, remotely toothed or entire, sparsely pubescent or almost glabrous beneath. Flowers in narrow, pendent panicles up to 25 cm. Calyx-teeth longer than wide. Corolla lilac, the tube curved and densely pubescent outside.{\i  Sometimes cultivated for ornament and occasionally naturalized in France}. [Ga.] ({\i Japan}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. B. lindleyana} Fortune ex Lindley,{\i  Bot. Reg. }{\b 30} ({\i Misc}.): 25 (1844). Like {\b 3} but twigs not or narrowly winged; flowers in erect panicles; calyx-teeth as wide as long; corolla purple, the tube floccose outside.{\i  Sometimes cultivated for ornament and occasionally naturalized in France.} [Ga.] ({\i China.})
